<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-6613 SERIES - INSTALL -
        YOKE/COMPANION FLANGE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>YOKE/COMPANION FLANGE</title>
        <para>Install the speedometer drive gear or replacement spacer on the hub of the yoke or flange. Lock the
            transmission in two speeds and install the yoke or flange on the splines of the output shaft. Install the
            output nut and tighten to 450 to 500 ft-lbs. (610 to 678 N&#183;m) (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13030r5">Figure 275</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f13030r5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13030r5" filename="../figg13/g13030r5.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 274. Install Output Nut and Tighten</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
